Package com.example.chicksevent

Class OrganizerNotifTest

java.lang.Object
com.example.chicksevent.OrganizerNotifTest
public class OrganizerNotifTest extends Object
Unit tests for Organizer related to user story US 02.07.02: "As an organizer I want to send notifications to all selected entrants."

These tests are designed to run synchronously By mocking Firebase Realtime Database we ensure deterministic behaviour of Organizer.sendSelectedNotification(String) and Organizer.sendWaitingListNotificationHelper(com.example.chicksevent.enums.EntrantStatus, String) without awaiting asynchronous callbacks.

Key Behaviours Verified

  • sendSelectedNotification(String) delegates correctly to the INVITED bucket
  • sendCancelledNotification(String) delegates correctly to the CANCELLED bucket
  • sendWaitingListNotificationHelper(...) builds a List of Notification objects, one per entrant in the requested waiting-list bucket
  • Each constructed Notification carries the correct userId, eventId, message, and NotificationType derived from the EntrantStatus
  • Graceful handling of empty buckets (returns an empty list when no entrants exist)

Testing Approach

  • Mocks FirebaseDatabase.getInstance(String) to prevent real Firebase initialization
  • Provides mocked DatabaseReference chains for the "WaitingList", "Organizer", "Event", and "User" roots used inside Organizer
  • Replaces Task.continueWith(Continuation) with synchronous lambda evaluation to immediately execute continuations with controlled DataSnapshot trees

All Firebase references and snapshot traversals are simulated to guarantee full control over test inputs and outputs, ensuring safe and deterministic verification of the organizer's notification-broadcast logic in a local JVM environment.
